Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Trim ends from @zucchini{2}(trimmed, halved lengthwise, and sliced into ¼-inch-thick half-moons). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Cut @roma tomatoes{2}(cut into 1-inch-thick wedges). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Toss zucchini and onion on a #baking sheet{} with half the garlic, @Tuscan heat spice{½%tbsp} (we'll use more in step 4), a large drizzle of @olive oil{6%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until just softened, about ~{10%minutes}. Remove from oven and carefully push slices toward one side of baking sheet.

Toss tomatoes, a large drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper on empty side of baking sheet. Return to oven and roast until all veggies are browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Meanwhile, add @fusilli pasta{12%oz} to pot of boiling water. Cook until al dente, ~{10-12%minutes}. Reserve 1 1/2 cups pasta cooking water, then drain and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in pot used for pasta over medium-high heat. Add @chicken breast strips{20%oz} and season with a pinch of salt and pepper and @Tuscan heat spice{1%tbsp} (save the rest for another use). Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, about ~{5%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{4%tbsp} (we sent more) and remaining @garlic{2%cloves}(minced) to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @cream cheese{2%oz} and 1 cup pasta cooking water. Add fusilli, veggies, half the @Parmesan cheese{2%oz}, and @butter{2%tbsp}. Stir until well combined.

> TIP: Add more pasta cooking water, a little at a time, if needed to achieve a creamy consistency.

Remove from heat; season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between bowls. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and serve.